It might be because you have installed googletest to your operating system, and the version is too low for being used in ONNX Runtime.

I installed googletest both with `apt-get install googletest` (version 1.11.0-3) and building from source following their [README](https://github.com/google/googletest/blob/main/googletest/README.md) for version 1.13:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/google/googletest.git -b v1.13.0
cd googletest
mkdir build 
cd build
cmake ..
make
sudo make install
```

Yet I'm still getting the same errors. Perhaps ORT can't find googletest? Do you have any suggestions here?

Thanks for your help!
My suggestion is to use an isolated container: https://gist.github.com/seddonm1/5dc956b136a98b8d46d03ca205252b4a
You may build it without tests, or do the build in a clean environment that doesn't have googletest preinstalled.

Thank you both for the suggestions - they worked! I had some other stuff going on in my initial build, so I essentially re-built my Dockerfile piece by piece starting with the ORT installation. Everything worked as expected; it looks like I had some interference between packages in my initial build. Thanks!
